5. Which of the following classes of neurons are pseudounipolar?
That's right!  All other options are motor, and are therefore multipolar neurons.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

multipolar neuron:

most common; eg. motor neurons, which contact muscle, interneurons which communicate over short distances, etc.
numerous dendrites, single axon
information is received by dendrites, transferred via an axon to the synaptic terminals

(pseudo)unipolar neuron:

sensory neurons, which monitor body surfaces and internal organs
single process arises from cell body, divides into two branches
peripheral process begins as dendrites in a somatic or visceral target, which merge to from an axon
central process enters CNS, ends as synaptic terminals
again, information is received by dendrites, transferred via an axon to the synaptic terminals
